# Public marketing pages — design lock

These invariants protect the pre-launch public experience. **Do not change without explicit product approval.**

Enforced by E2E: `frontend/e2e/public-design-lock.spec.ts`  
Run: `npm run test:e2e -- public-design-lock` (from `frontend/`)

## Shell & styles

- `/`, `/coming-soon`, `/login`, and `/register` **MUST** use `PublicMarketingShell` from `frontend/src/components/PublicMarketingShell.tsx`.
- Shared tokens **MUST** come from `frontend/src/lib/publicStyles.ts` (`publicPanelClass`, `publicInputClass`, `publicNavLinkPrimary`, etc.).
- Do not reintroduce one-off layout grids or duplicate shell markup on these pages.

## Hero typography

- Hero headings **MUST** use `mr-hero-heading` + `mr-hero-accent` (Inter via `globals.css`).
- **Do NOT** use `mr-brand-wordmark`, Cinzel, or `--nn-font-display` on public hero `<h1>` elements.
- Prefer `PublicHeroBlock` for consistent hero structure.

## Landing (`/` and `/coming-soon`)

- **One** header sign-in link only: “Already have an invite? Sign in” → `/login`.
- **No** duplicate sign-in CTAs in the page body.
- **No** separate “JOIN THE WAITLIST” or “GET EARLY ACCESS” button rows — waitlist lives in the right panel only (“Join waitlist” submit).
- Canonical waitlist anchor: **`/coming-soon#waitlist`** (element `id="waitlist"`).
- **Beta 200** copy in the hero footer note must remain unless product explicitly removes it.

## Login & Register

- Header nav includes **Waitlist** linking to `/coming-soon#waitlist`.
- Form inputs use cream `publicInputClass` (`bg-[#F7EFE0]`).
- Keep mobile/desktop layout in sync via `PublicMarketingShell` — no separate mobile-only hero or CTA stacks.

## Before merging changes

1. Run `npm run build` in `frontend/`.
2. Run `npm run test:e2e -- public-design-lock`.
3. If tests fail, fix or get product sign-off — do not weaken assertions to “make green.”
